#1 Distal ascending colon adenocarcinoma
We discussed with Mrs. Hollis regarding the next step which is staging and meeting with a surgeon.  We will obtain preoperative laboratory testing, and also we will perform a CT-scan with IV contrast to evaluate staging.  We will see her back after these are completed.
#2 Perioperative evaluation
Given Mrs. Hollis's symptoms on the treadmill, I am concerned that these are angina or angina-like symptoms.  Given her aortic stenosis and the prior mild coronary disease seen on the CT-scan in 2007, we have requested an evaluation in Cardiology along with a stress echo cardiogram to be performed on a treadmill to further risk stratify her prior to her surgery.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, not on file at Palm Beach Gardens Hospital.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

